resources.description:
Located in the JSON tab of this POST command you will find the code shown below:
<pre><p style="color:green">{
	"name": "1st Test Collection",
	"description": "This Collection has been built via Insomnia",
	"tags": "test1",
	"business_unit": {
		"guid": "BU-GUID"
	},
	"custom_fields": null,
	"asset_infos": [
		{
			"guid": "APP1-GUID",
			"type": "APPLICATION"
		},
		{
			"guid": "APP2-GUID",
			"type": "APPLICATION"
		}
	]
}  
</pre></p>
Do the following:
<ol><li>In the "name:" field replace <i style="color:green">1st Test Collection</i> with the name you want to give to the Collection being created (keep the quotes)
	<li>In the "description:" field replace <i style="color:green">This Collection has been built via Insomnia</i> with the description you want to give to the Collection being created (keep the quotes)
		<li>In the "tags:" field replace <i style="color:green">test1</i> with the tags value(s) you want to give to the Collection being created (keep the quotes)
			<li>In the "business_unit" field replace <i style="color:green">BU_GUID</i> with the GUID value of the Buisness Unit to which this Collection will belong (this was copied/pasted according the directions in 1-collectionsGetAppGUID)
			<li>In the "asset_infos:" section replace <i style="color:green">APP1-GUID</i> with the GUID value of the application to be added (this was copied/pasted according the directions in 1-collectionsGetAppGUID)
				<li>The followwing text should be copied and pasted, at the end of the json code, as many times as needed to add all of the applications required to be in the collection.  Each time replacing the <i style="color:green">APP2-GUID</i> with the GUID value of the additional application to be added (this was copied/pasted according the directions in 1-collectionsGetAppGUID)</ol>
					<pre><p style="color:green"> 

		{
			"guid": "APP2-GUID",
			"type": "APPLICATION"
		}
</pre></p>

